Poland May Raise 1.5 Billion Zloty from BGZ Sale, Rp.pl Says

-- B y   M a r t a   W a l d o c h
-- 
2011-04-18T05:12:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-18/poland-may-raise-1-5-billion-zloty-from-bgz-sale-rp-pl-says.html
The Polish government, which is
selling its remaining 37 percent stake in Bank Gospodarki
Zywnosciowej SA, may raise from 1 billion zloty ($360 million)
to 1.5 billion zloty from May’s planned sale,  Rzeczpospolita 
reported.  Espirito Santo Investments, one of the Polish Treasury
Ministry’s advisers on the sale, values the bank, also known as
BGZ, at 3.02 billion zloty to 3.96 billion zloty, Rzeczpospolita
said.  Bank Handlowy SA estimates the bank is worth from 2.28
billion zloty to 3.2 billion zloty, the newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marta Waldoch in Warsaw on 
 mwaldoch@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at   fconnelly@bloomberg.net  